<!-- ═══ S9 KILL RULES ═══ -->
<div class="slide cs" id="s9">
  <div class="sh"><h2>Kill Rules + The Ashton "Launch 50, Run 10" Hack</h2><span class="st">Section 02 — KPIs &amp; Testing</span></div>
  <div class="sb">
    <div class="g2" style="flex-shrink:0;">
      <div class="metric red" style="text-align:left;padding:14px 18px;"><div class="m-label">New Ad Kill Threshold</div><div class="m-val">2× KPI</div><div class="m-desc">Spend 2x cost per KPI before killing. Target $375/call? Spend $750 first. Not $50. Not $2,000.</div></div>
      <div class="metric orange" style="text-align:left;padding:14px 18px;"><div class="m-label">Existing Winner Kill Threshold</div><div class="m-val">3× KPI</div><div class="m-desc">Give proven winners more room. Bad week ≠ dead ad. 3x threshold protects winners from premature cuts.</div></div>
    </div>
    <div style="flex:1;overflow:hidden;">
      <table class="dt">
        <thead><tr><th>Scenario</th><th>Action</th><th>Why</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><strong>Hook rate under 15%</strong></td><td><span class="badge br">Kill or Fix Hook Only</span></td><td>Body may be fine. Swap first 3 seconds only. Keep the same script body. Don't rebuild the whole ad.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Good hook, low hold rate</strong></td><td><span class="badge bn">Fix — Don't Kill</span></td><td>Add re-hook at 10-12s. Move CTA to 30-45s mark. These are different problems with different solutions.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>New ad, 2× KPI, no result</strong></td><td><span class="badge br">Kill It</span></td><td>It had its chance. Make a new entity — don't edit this one. Editing resets the ad ID learning.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Winner struggling</strong></td><td><span class="badge bo">Wait for 3× KPI</span></td><td>One bad week proves nothing. Give it more room before pulling the plug on something that's worked.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>NEVER edit a live winning ad</strong></td><td><span class="badge br">Duplicate Instead</span></td><td>Edit the ad ID = reset all micro-learning. Duplicate winner → edit the copy → launch as new ad.</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <div style="background:#0f172a;border-radius:10px;padding:14px 20px;flex-shrink:0;">
      <div style="font-family:'DM Mono';font-size:10px;color:var(--orange);margin-bottom:8px;letter-spacing:1px;">ASHTON PRO HACK — LAUNCH 50, RUN 10</div>
      <div style="font-size:12px;color:var(--blue-light);line-height:1.55;">Launch all test ads at once (up to 50). Turn 40 off immediately. Run 10 active. When a loser dies → turn one of the 40 on → <strong style="color:white;">no learning phase reset.</strong> This is the most underused tactical hack in this room. Plan ahead and you never have to restart learning.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
